title: Bulldog Women Win Conference XC Title
text:
Bulldog Women Win Conference XC Title 
By Norman Seawright III Bulldog Women Win Conference XC Title October 24, 2015 Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 9:07 PM CDT 
Falcon Heights, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) women's cross country team won its second Northern Sun Intercollegiate Conference (NSIC) title in three years, while the men's team placed fifth in the conference title meet. 
Junior Breanna Colbenson led the team in the six-kilometer race by placing fifth (22:39.3), followed by sophomore Emilee Olson in sixth (22:43.1) and senior Hannah Olson in seventh (22:43.9), all of whom earned all-NSIC first team honors.
